  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Big 3 Ski Area Ski Resorts<br /></strong></p>
<p>Stunning mountain backdrops, occasional wildlife sightings, uncrowded slopes and friendly local hospitality are just some of the big attractions of this amazing ski area in the heart of the majestic Canadian Rockies. Banff’s family-friendly ‘home’ mountain, Mount Norquay, the huge Lake Louise area and high altitude Sunshine Village are all on the one convenient ‘Tri-Area’ lift-pass, which also includes the free ski-bus service connecting all three areas.</p>
<p><strong>Skiing in the Big 3 Ski Area<br /></strong></p>
<p>These ‘Ski Big Three’ resorts combine to offer some of Canada’s best and most varied skiing and boarding, with terrain to suit every level, from gentle groomed runs to some of the world’s most extreme challenges, such as the aptly named ‘Delirium Dive’ run, and snow-parks for free-ski and boarding fun.</p>
<p><strong>Ski Holidays in <strong>the Big 3 Ski Area</strong><br /></strong></p>
<p>You can stay in the following resorts (accommodation linked below) for the Big 3 Ski Area ski holidays:</p>
<p><strong>Banff</strong></p>
<p>Banff is the heart and soul of Canada’s greatest and most famous National Park. Hotels here range from outstanding value, friendly 3-stars right up to the majestic castle-like Banff Springs Hotel – a Rockies icon in its own right. The nightlife is friendly and varied, and there is an incredible choice of restaurants for dining out, across all price ranges and cuisines.. (More info on <strong><a href="/{localLink:9c51e652-9587-4c04-850d-7d91aa9a068b}" title="Banff">Banff</a></strong>)</p>
<p><strong>Lake Louise</strong></p>
<p>Lake Louise village has limited facilities beyond our choice of hotels, but guests here prize the sensationally beautiful wilderness location above rowdy nightlife, and the hotels between them offer an ample choice of bars and restaurants to enjoy in the evenings. It is also often the keen skier’s choice, with Lake Louise’s own nearby area offering over 4,200 acres of varied terrain!. (More info on <strong><a href="/{localLink:f93758d2-3601-4e72-b27a-5c3261e64d25}" title="Lake Louise">Lake Louise</a></strong>)</p>]]></generalInformation>
